 Ahead of the World AIDS Day, which falls on Wednesday, the Joint United Nations Programme on HIV/AIDS (UNAIDS) issued a stark warning saying that if leaders fail to tackle inequalities the world could face 7.7 million AIDS-related deaths over the next 10 years. We talk to Winnie Byanyima, UNAIDS executive director and an Under-Secretary-General of the United Nations on this and more. Produced by Xinhua Global Serviceâ–  